  "is_vocab": false,
  "stimulus_html": "<p><small style=\"font-variant: small-caps\">L</small>-Fucose, one of the eight essential monosaccharides (<b>Section 25.7</b>), is biosynthesized from GDP-<small style=\"font-variant: small-caps\">D</small>-mannose by the following three-step reaction sequence, where GDP = guanosine diphosphate (a ribonucleoside diphosphate; <b>Section 28.1</b>):</p>\n<img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBb0laIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--69b6c7f775541ae7e57d32c3673adab5e09709fe/OChem_25_EC_011.jpg\" alt=\"G D P- L-Fucose, one of the essential monosaccharides, is biosynthesized from G D P - D-mannose by a three-step reaction sequence.\">",
  "questions": [
    {
      "id": 358798,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "Step 1 involves an oxidation to a ketone, a dehydration to an enone, and a conjugate reduction. The step requires NADP<sup>+</sup>, but no NADPH is formed as a final reaction product. Propose a mechanism.",
